{% comment %}
  SEO Homepage H1 Fix — ByErim

  PURPOSE:
  The current homepage H1 reads "Stories from our Community" which tells Google
  the page is about community stories, not hair oil. This snippet adds a proper
  SEO-optimised H1 that is visually styled to match the brand but readable by
  Google as the primary topic.

  INSTALL:
  In the homepage template (templates/index.json or sections/hero.liquid),
  add this snippet at the very top of the hero/banner section — BEFORE the
  current first heading.

  The <h1> below replaces whatever is currently the first H1 on the page.
  The existing "Stories from our Community" heading should be demoted to <h2>.
{% endcomment %}

<h1 class="seo-h1 visually-prominent">
  Natural Ayurvedic Hair Oil &amp; Award-Winning Hair Care | ByErim
</h1>

{% comment %}
  Optional: if the brand wants this visually hidden but still crawlable,
  wrap in a sr-only class. But ideally keep it visible — it reinforces the brand.
  
  Suggested CSS (add to base.css or theme.css):
  
  .seo-h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--color-foreground);
    margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
    max-width: 800px;
    padding: 0 1rem;
  }
{% endcomment %}
